description: The India Meteorological Department issued health risk warnings due to a heatwave affecting Konkan, Vidarbha in Maharashtra, and southwest Rajasthan. Temperatures have soared above normal, with Pune reaching 40.2°C. Vulnerable populations are advised to avoid heat exposure and stay hydrated. Some regions might see a temperature decline from Thursday, as Maharashtra's Akola reached 41.3°C, the state's highest.
title: A heatwave is on, guard against illnesses: IMD
Calculators for Std 12 exam on accountancy? CBSE to decide
HC upholds TISS suspension of PhD student for misconduct, stir
Indian Muslims are patriotic, says Ajit Pawar

description: The Karnataka government withdrew its approval for a CID probe into the police escort given to actor Ranya Rao at Bengaluru airport. This decision came within 24 hours of the announcement, allegedly due to pressure, and is now handled by senior IAS officer Gaurav Gupta.
title: Karnataka nixes CID probe into police escort for Ranya Rao

description: Socialite Shalini Passi has been summoned by the Meerut unit of Directorate General of GST Intelligence in a case of alleged GST evasion linked to Pasco Motors LLP. Allegations involve split invoicing to apply different GST rates. Her lawyer denies the accusations, which have been challenged in court. Further investigation and compliance are awaited.
title: Socialite called for quizzing in ‘GST evasion case’

description: Uttarakhand High Court acquitted a polio-affected man convicted of rape and ordered the state government to compensate him with Rs 5 lakh due to investigation flaws. The man, an employee at a cybercafe, had been serving a 20-year prison sentence. The court cited his physical condition making the charges questionable and found improper police investigation.
title: Uttarakhand HC acquits polio-hit man of rape over flawed probe

description: The Trump White House flagged India's 150% tariff on American bourbon, despite India lowering it to 100% ahead of Modi's Washington visit. This move, aimed at highlighting reciprocity in trade, comes as Trump simultaneously promotes Tesla's potential entry into India, while the WHO advises that no level of alcohol consumption is safe for health.
title: White House throws bourbon brickbat at India
U’khand HC halts felling of 3k+ trees for Rishikesh-Bhaniawala road expansion

description: Authorities at Banke Bihari temple in Vrindavan have dismissed a proposal to ban dresses made by Muslim weavers for Lord Krishna, emphasizing the importance of the purity of the attire. They stated that devotees from all backgrounds are welcome to contribute, provided they have faith in Thakurji.
title: Banke Bihari temple rejects call to ban Muslim-made attire for deity

description: Interpol red corner notice led to the arrest of Lithuanian national Aleksej Besciokov at Varkala, Kerala, for financial fraud in the US. Besciokov, a co-founder of the cryptocurrency exchange Garantex, is accused of laundering billions through criminal organizations and faces an indictment unsealed by the US justice department.
title: Crypto fraudster wanted in US arrested in Kerala

description: A dispute over parking in Mohali's Sector 66 led to the death of 39-year-old scientist Abhishek Swarnkar. His neighbour Monty assaulted him despite knowing his fragile health. The incident was captured on CCTV. Swarnkar was declared dead upon arrival at the hospital. Police have registered a case, and further legal action is pending.
title: IISER scientist killed after parking dispute with neighbour in Mohali
Odisha villagers use drone to nab thief

description: Maharashtra's transport minister, Pratap Sarnaik, admitted that employees' provident fund and gratuity were used to cover daily expenses and salary hikes for the Maharashtra State Road Transport Corporation. The opposition demanded a complaint against the MSRTC's managing director. Sarnaik assured that future improper use of funds would be avoided and employees would not lose interest on diverted money.
title: Rs 2,200 crore PF-gratuity fund spent on wages: Maha transport minister
Senior BHEL officer found dead in office with bullet injury
US filmmaker mocks Indian passengers says 'classic flight landing in India'

description: BJP dominated the municipal polls in Haryana, winning nine out of ten mayoral seats. Woman candidates secured seven mayoral positions. CM Nayab Singh Saini hailed the outcome as public endorsement. Congress suffered setbacks, including in Rohtak. Some independent candidates also triumphed, notably in Manesar and Faridabad. BJP claimed 90% of councillor seats.
title: With 9 of 10 Haryana mayoral seats, BJP humbles Congress
44 years on, 3 found guilty of 25 Dalits’ killings in Dehuli

description: Republican lawmakers are calling for investigations into recent vandalism targeting Tesla showrooms and charging stations. President Donald Trump supports these measures, suggesting that such acts could be labeled as domestic terrorism. House Speaker Mike Johnson announced Congress will work with the Justice Department and FBI to address the incidents.
title: Donald Trump makes a 'Big Tesla Terrorism' announcement, says 'I will ...'

description: Jayson Tatum is questionable for the Boston Celtics' game against the Oklahoma City Thunder on March 12. His absence would be a significant blow due to injuries to other key players. The game is scheduled for 7:30 p.m. ET, and fans are eagerly awaiting updates on Tatum’s status, which could be crucial for the Celtics.
title: Will Jayson Tatum play tonight agianst the OKC Thunder?

description: Amazon Prime Video is now streaming reruns of 'The Apprentice,' the reality show starring Donald Trump, starting with its first season. New seasons will be released weekly, with the seventh season coming in April.
title: Amazon Prime Video is bringing Trump starrer ‘The Apprentice’: All details

description: Connor McDavid, captain of the Edmonton Oilers, is facing criticism from fans after showing frustration during a loss to the Buffalo Sabres. Fans are questioning his leadership, blaming poor team direction and netminding. Some fans also criticize head coach Kris Knoblauch for not calling a timeout. The Oilers are preparing to face the New Jersey Devils next.
title: Connor McDavid’s frustration sparks debate over his leadership

description: Kashmir's Chinar trees are being digitally tagged with unique numbers and QR codes by the J&K Forest Research Institute to track and monitor their health and presence. This initiative aims to combat illegal felling and urbanization threats. So far, 28,560 Chinars have been recorded, including some of the oldest and largest in Asia.
title: Digital Aadhaar shields Kashmir’s Chinars from axe of greed

description: Elon Musk has expressed concern about South Korea's declining population, highlighting the country's low fertility rate of 0.68. He warned of a 'catastrophic population collapse' and stated that immigration is not a sustainable solution.
title: Elon Musk makes another ‘catastrophic population collapse’ warning, this time for …

description: The ministry of home affairs has returned a proposal to prosecute three IAS officers in the Jammu and Kashmir arms licences scam due to missing documents. They must resubmit the full documentation within a week. CBI is investigating irregularities in granting over 278,000 arms licences between 2012 and 2016, implicating several IAS officers for issuing licences in exchange for money.
title: J&K arms licence scam: MHA denies nod for 3 IAS officers prosecution
'President is salesman now': Democrat slams Trump for 'buying, promoting' Tesla car

description: Pakistan's military killed all Baloch Liberation Army terrorists and freed 300 hostages in Balochistan. The militant group hijacked the Jaffar Express train. The operation left 21 hostages dead due to militant actions. The train had over 450 passengers including security personnel. The terrorists were in contact with their leaders in Afghanistan.
title: Retaking of the Jaffar Express: Pak forces kill all ‘terrorists’; 21 hostages slain by BLA

description: An Indian Army soldier stationed at the Line of Control in Jammu and Kashmir was injured by cross-border firing from Pakistan in the Rajouri district. The incident occurred at Kalsiyan of Nowshera sector. Another explosion took place in the Poonch district later, though no casualties were reported.
title: Soldier hit by bullet from across LoC in J&K’s Rajouri

description: Airtel and Jio have joined hands with Elon Musk's Starlink to bring satellite internet services to India. This partnership aims to enhance digital connectivity in rural and remote areas, providing online education, telemedicine, and disaster relief. Starlink's low Earth orbit satellites offer a solution where traditional infrastructure fails, emphasizing technology in promoting economic development.
title: Airtel, Jio to bring Elon Musk’s Starlink in India: What this means for users

description: Pakistan's security forces freed hostages and eliminated 33 militants involved in a train hijacking in Balochistan. The militants derailed the Jaffar Express, killing 21 passengers and four soldiers. The coordinated rescue operation took nearly 24 hours and ensured the safety of all passengers. The government promises to deal with all facilitators of these terrorists.
title: How Pak forces rescued hostages used as human shields in train siege
Pak train hijack: 'BLA militants were in contact with masterminds in Kabul'

description: The Karnataka government withdrew the CID probe into police involvement in the Ranya Rao gold smuggling case. A Bengaluru court reserved its bail plea verdict for March 14, with allegations of procedural lapses during her arrest, while the DRI disputed such claims. Gold worth ₹12.56 crore was seized from her.
title: Ranya Rao smuggling case: K'taka govt withdraws CID probe into police role
'Welcome to India': Minister Vaishnaw's message for Starlink

description: Despite India's recent reduction of tariffs on American bourbon, the Trump administration insists the 100% duty is still unhelpful. The White House highlights that this discrepancy impacts US spirits market expansion, emphasizing the need for fair treatment of American businesses globally.
title: After bikes, booze: White House whines about whiskey exports to India

description: NASA and SpaceX are launching the Crew-10 mission today to the ISS, carrying astronauts from NASA, JAXA, and Roscosmos. This mission will also bring back NASA's Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore, who were stranded in space for eight months due to technical issues with Boeing's Starliner. The mission will focus on scientific research and technological experiments.
title: Nasa's Sunita Williams finally returning to Earth

description: Pakistan PM Shehbaz Sharif condemned the Jaffar Express hijacking by Baloch Liberation Army, calling it a cowardly act that won't deter the nation's resolve for peace. The attack resulted in the death of several hostages and militants, with ongoing rescue operations saving 190 passengers so far.
title: 'Such acts won't shake Pak’s resolve for peace': PM Sharif on train hijack

description: US President Donald Trump purchased a Tesla Model S to support Elon Musk amid declining Tesla stock and attacks on the company. Trump praised Musk for his dedication and suggested labeling attackers of Tesla as 'domestic terrorists.' Following his gesture, Tesla stock rose by 7% and Musk committed to doubling US production within two years.
title: Trump tests ethical boundaries by buying Tesla to bail out Musk
What is 'Mahasagar' vision? New policy unveiled by PM Modi
Who is Joshua Riibe, man linked to missing Indian-origin Sudiksha Konanki’s disappearance

description: Dalit families in a West Bengal village have been allowed to worship at the Gidheshwar Shiv Temple for the first time in nearly 300 years, breaking a significant caste barrier. Despite initial resistance and economic boycotts, intervention by local authorities facilitated this historic event.
title: After 300 yrs, Dalit families enter Gidheshwar Shiv Temple in Bengal

description: Sanju Samson, captain of Rajasthan Royals, shares his experiences and admiration for former Indian captain MS Dhoni, while expressing enthusiasm about RR's young talent, Vaibhav Suryavanshi. Samson highlights his evolving relationship with Dhoni and praises 13-year-old Vaibhav's power-hitting abilities and potential in the IPL, boasting his impressive performance and promising future.
title: 'Always wanted to be around Mahi bhai': Samson on bond with Dhoni

description: Cognizant has begun informing eligible employees about their bonus payouts, with amounts ranging between 85% and 115%. Bonuses will be disbursed in March and April based on individual country payroll schedules. Merit pay increases will take effect from August 2025. Infosys has also given salary hikes based on performance, with increases ranging from 5% to 20%.
title: Cognizant starts sending bonus letters to eligible employees; says it is ...

description: Former Pakistan cricketer Imad Wasim has criticised Pakistan's outdated playing style following their poor performance in the ICC Champions Trophy. He highlighted that modern cricket requires an aggressive approach and that Pakistan has failed to adapt. Imad warned that continuing to play cautiously would result in losing fan interest and called for a complete overhaul of their cricketing approach.
title: 'Don't want to watch the team play': Ex-Pak cricketer slams 'outdated' style

description: Uttar Pradesh chief minister Yogi Adityanath expressed his pride in wearing saffron attire, predicting its global acceptance. He spoke on the Sambhal mosque controversy, stressing the historical significance of the Vishnu temple predating Islam and questioned opposition leaders' commitment to preserving cultural and religious heritage.
title: 'Entire world will wear bhagwa': UP CM says Saffron is his identity

description: Former Pakistan cricketer Basit Ali has revealed his ICC Champions Trophy playing XI, with India's Rohit Sharma as captain. His team focuses on performances in Dubai and differs from the official ICC team. Ali highlighted key performances, especially Sharma's 76 in the final, and included other top players like Virat Kohli and Shreyas Iyer.
title: Ex-Pak cricketer picks Champions Trophy XI with no Pakistani players

description: Holi celebrates the triumph of righteousness and the arrival of spring, marked by mythological significance and vibrant traditions. The festival includes the burning of negativity on Holika Dahan and joyous color play on Rangwali Holi. Celebrations vary across India, fostering unity and new beginnings. Holi is celebrated over two days, each with its own special rituals.
title: Happy Holi 2025: Best messages, quotes, wishes and images to share

description: Senior Awami League leader Rabbi Alam has claimed that Sheikh Hasina will return as the prime minister of Bangladesh. He thanked India for providing a safe haven for Hasina, who fled last year after violent clashes. Mohammed Yunus led the interim government and sought Hasina's extradition, which India hasn't officially responded to yet.
title: 'Hasina coming back as PM': Why Awami League leader thanked India
IAF to get indigenous low-level transportable radars under Rs 2,906cr deal

description: Former Pakistan cricketer Kamran Akmal criticised the absence of a Pakistani representative during the ICC Champions Trophy prize distribution, attributing it to the team's subpar performance. The PCB lodged a complaint with the ICC, but officials defended the protocol, stating that it did not require the presence of the tournament director on stage.
title: 'ICC showed us the mirror': Akmal says Pak didn't deserve stage presence at CT ceremony

description: Mahmudullah, a celebrated Bangladeshi cricketer, has announced his retirement from international cricket, capping a 17-year career. He expressed gratitude to his supporters and family in his announcement. Notably, Mahmudullah holds the distinction of being the only Bangladeshi to score three centuries in ODI World Cups.
title: Mahmudullah announces retirement from international cricket

description: Zerodha CEO Nithin Kamath revealed that the company is experiencing its first business slowdown in 15 years. A decline in active users across major stock broking platforms signifies a broader market correction. According to National Stock Exchange (NSE) data, eight of the top 10 broking firms saw a decline in active investors in February.  Kamath noted a 30% drop in trading activity due to market conditions and regulatory changes.
title: Nithin Kamath said Zerodha users drop in 15 years; Groww may just agree

description: Dattatray Gade, accused of raping a 26-year-old woman in a parked MSRTC bus at Pune's Swargate terminus, has been remanded to police custody until March 26. The arrest followed an extensive manhunt with Gade attempting suicide multiple times before being captured. Authorities are investigating security lapses at the terminus, while protests and calls for swift justice continue.
title: Pune bus rape case: Accused remanded to judicial custody till March 26

description: BJP leader Amit Malviya shared a photo linking Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah with actress Ranya Rao, who is accused in a gold smuggling case. Malviya took a dig at Deputy CM DK Shivakumar, who had earlier denied any political connection to the case, further escalating tensions.
title: Ranya Rao gold case: BJP shares photo to back Cong link claim

description: Tamil Nadu CM M K Stalin criticized the National Education Policy, calling it a "saffron policy" designed to promote Hindi over regional languages, particularly Tamil. "National Education Policy is not education policy; it is saffron policy. The policy is not created to develop India but to develop Hindi. We are opposing the policy as it would destroy the Tamil Nadu education system completely," Stalin said.
title: 'Saffron policy': CM Stalin blasts NEP, vows to fight 'BJP's fascism'

description: SBI has announced technical disruptions affecting its online services, including UPI, since March 12, 2025. Customers are urged to use UPI lite services during this period. Online banking and mobile banking are significantly impacted. This issue follows a similar disruption the day before, with ongoing efforts to resolve the problems. Stay updated through SBI's official channels.
title: SBI down: Here’s what the bank has to say

description: The BJP secured a sweeping victory in Haryana’s civic polls, winning key cities like Ambala, Faridabad, and Gurugram. CM Nayab Singh Saini called the results a public endorsement of the "triple-engine government" driving rapid development. He reaffirmed PM Modi’s vision of a "Viksit Bharat" by 2047 and pledged to fulfill the BJP’s poll promise, including financial aid for women under the 'Lado Lakshmi Yojana.'
title: 'Stamp of approval': BJP vows development after sweeping Haryana civic polls

description: The ICC praised the Pakistan Cricket Board for successfully hosting the ICC Men's Champions Trophy 2025, marking Pakistan's first ICC event since 1996. India won the tournament, which saw 15 matches played across Karachi, Lahore, Rawalpindi and Dubai. The event showcased Pakistan's passion for cricket and ability to host global events, drawing fans worldwide.
title: 'Thank You Pakistan': ICC lauds PCB for successful Champions Trophy

description: Pakistan is experiencing a severe security crisis, fighting four interconnected militant groups: Tehrik-i-Taliban Pakistan, Balochistan Liberation Army, Islamic State Khorasan, and the influence of the Afghan Taliban. Terrorism-related deaths and attacks have surged, leading to significant instability and geopolitical concerns, including threats to Chinese investments. The country must urgently adapt its counterterrorism strategy to maintain stability.
title: TTP, BLA, ISK, Taliban: Will Pakistan succumb to 'Quad of terror'?

description: Ukraine has agreed to a 30-day ceasefire proposed by the US, potentially pausing the three-year war with Russia if Moscow reciprocates. High-stakes negotiations in Saudi Arabia led to Washington resuming military aid to Kyiv. Putin's acceptance remains uncertain, with concerns about Russia's historical ceasefire violations and demands for territorial concessions.
title: Ukraine ready for 30-day ceasefire: Will Putin 'tango' with Trump?

description: Retail inflation in February dropped to a 7-month low of 3.61%. It remains within the RBI's target. Food inflation also saw significant reductions in both rural and urban areas. This decline may encourage the Monetary Policy Committee to cut the repo rate in April to boost GDP growth.
title: Retail CPI inflation eases to 7-month low of 3.61% in Feb; Jan IIP growth at 5%

description: Survivors of the Jaffar Express attack by the Balochistan Liberation Army recounted the horror of being hijacked and enduring intense gunfire. The female and elderly were spared, while security personnel and Punjabis were targeted. Security forces rescued 190 hostages from the 450 passengers. Violence has escalated in Balochistan against non-Baloch Pakistanis, with the BLA intensifying attacks.
title: 'Felt like doomsday': Survivors recall BLA's terrifying attack on Pak train

description: A political controversy has started in Maharashtra over the government's new 'Malhar Certification' initiative. Minister Nitesh Rane launched this certification for Hindu meat traders to ensure shops are 100% Hindu-owned and free from adulteration. Opposition leaders have criticised the move, calling it divisive and unconstitutional. Rane defended the initiative, focusing on ensuring quality and promoting Hindu-owned businesses.
title: Halal vs Malhar: What is the row that has rocked Maharashtra politics?

description: Shubman Gill has been named the ICC Men’s Player of the Month for February 2025 after impressive ODI performances, amassing 406 runs in five matches. His stellar displays, including a century against England and a crucial knock in the Champions Trophy, have solidified his position as the world’s top ODI batter.
title: World No.1 Shubman Gill crowned ICC Player of the Month

description: During his visit to Mauritius, Prime Minister Narendra Modi was honored with the nation's highest award, dedicating it to the Indian ancestors of Mauritius and all generations. Modi emphasized his commitment to strengthening the India-Mauritius partnership and jointly inaugurated the Atal Bihari Vajpayee Institute of Public Service and Innovation.
title: PM Modi receives Mauritius' highest award; 8 pacts signed

description: Hardik Pandya lifted the ICC Champions Trophy in 2025, eight years after his valiant 76-run knock in the 2017 final against Pakistan ended in defeat. Pandya expressed joy and determination, eager for more titles. Celebrating the team’s effort, he aims for India to win the 2026 ICC T20 World Cup on home soil.
title: 'Need 5-6 more trophies': Hardik after winning CT & T20 WC in a short span

description: The Baloch Liberation Army hijacked a passenger train in Pakistan's Balochistan province, detonating an explosive to halt the train and taking passengers hostage. Pakistani security forces managed to rescue 155 passengers, while 27 militants were killed in the ensuing standoff. The situation remains critical as insurgents still hold hostages.
title: Watch: How Baloch insurgents blew up tracks, hijacked Pak train

description: Several F1 experts have tagged McLaren as the favorite for the upcoming season, with Mika Hakkinen endorsing Lando Norris as a potential world champion. Both Norris and teammate Oscar Piastri aim to impress, leveraging McLaren's superior MCL39 supercar.
title: 'I believe Lando Norris is ready': Mika Hakkinen on McLaren driver

description: India won the ICC Men’s Champions Trophy 2025 by defeating New Zealand in the final. The victory led to several Indian and New Zealand players climbing up the ICC Men’s ODI Player Rankings. Shubman Gill and Rohit Sharma made notable gains among batters, while Mitchell Santner and Kuldeep Yadav rose in the bowling rankings.
title: Rohit rises to no. 3 in ODI rankings after CT final heroics

description: Uttar Pradesh CM Yogi Adityanath urged people to stop glorifying foreign invaders, stressing the importance of preserving religious sites like Sambhal. Speaking in Lucknow, he emphasized the need to respect places of worship and criticized those who forcibly occupy them. He also highlighted the significance of the Maha Kumbh and criticized previous administrations for mismanagement.
title: 'Only 18 of 68 sites found': CM Yogi hints at more excavations in Sambhal
Nitish consumes 'bhang': Rabri, Tejashwi's big 'bindi', lewd gesture charge against CM

description: Ranveer Allahbadia's controversial question on parental sex in a show has sparked a debate on the need for censorship in OTT platforms. Industry experts suggest that self-regulation and parental guidance might be better approaches than strict censorship. The key is finding a balance between creative freedom and content moderation to protect vulnerable audiences.
title: Post Ranveer Allahbadia controversy, does OTT content also need regulations?

description: Students at Osmania University protested after allegedly finding a razor blade in a curry served at their hostel mess. They demanded an immediate response from the Vice Chancellor. In response, university authorities set up a committee to investigate the incident.
title: Razor blade found in mess curry, Osmania University hostel launch stir

description: A man driving a Thar caused havoc in Noida when he fled recklessly after an argument about installing speakers. The viral video shows the Thar hitting several vehicles without slowing down. Police have registered a complaint and formed teams to apprehend the driver.
title: Watch: Thar driver goes on rampage in Noida, hits vehicles after tiff over speakers

description: Greenland’s centre-right opposition, the Democrats, emerged victorious with 29.9% votes, while the nationalist Naleraq party followed closely.
title: Greenland polls: Opposition party Democrats wins amid Trump's 'acquire' threat

description: BJP MLA Haribhushan Thakur criticized Darbhanga mayor Anjum Ara for her Holi advisory, calling it a display of 'terrorist mentality'. Ara requested a two-hour break in Holi festivities to coincide with Friday prayers during Ramzan. Thakur insists Holi celebrations will proceed uninterrupted, warning of strict actions against any disruptions.
title: 'Woman of terrorist mentality': BJP MLA on Darbhanga mayor over Holi request

description: Following the inauguration of Donald Trump, financial setbacks have plagued five major billionaires, with a combined loss of $209 billion. Tesla’s Elon Musk has seen his wealth plummet by $148 billion, while Jeff Bezos and Sergey Brin also face substantial declines. Market uncertainties and government policies are factors impacting their fortunes.
title: Musk to Bezos, billionaires who attended Trump’s inauguration face $209 billion loss

description: Shahjahanpur is preparing for ‘Laat Sahab’ Holi on March 14 with extensive security measures. Around 3,500 security personnel, drones, and CCTV cameras will ensure safety. Authorities emphasize cooperation for a peaceful celebration.
title: Mosques covered ahead of Laat Sahab Holi in UP's Shahjahanpur

description: The Allahabad High Court allows whitewashing and decorative lighting of Sambhal Jama Masjid’s exterior, with no structural changes. ASI is tasked with inspecting the site and reporting the necessity of these changes. The court has scheduled the next hearing for April 8.
title: Allahabad HC allows whitewashing, lighting of Sambhal Jama Masjid exterior

description: A heated exchange occurred between White House Press Secretary Karoline Leavitt and AP reporter Josh Boak regarding Trump's tariff policies. Leavitt defended the tariffs, claiming they benefit American workers and are not tax hikes. Boak countered, stating tariffs impact importers, not foreign companies. The interaction highlights ongoing tension between the Trump administration and the AP.
title: Have you ever paid a tariff? Trump press secretary's heated exchange with reporter

description: IBM CEO Arvind Krishna at SXSW conference asserted AI will enhance programmer productivity rather than replacing them soon. He predicted AI might automate 20-30% of code, contrary to Anthropic's forecast of 90%. Although IBM plans to halt hiring for roles prone to AI automation, Krishna highlighted AI's potential to boost output and market share.
title: IBM CEO may have just 'disagreed' with his 'AI warning' for techies

description: Authorities in Virginia have identified 24-year-old Joshua Ribe as a person of interest in the disappearance of University of Pittsburgh student Sudiksha Konanki in the Dominican Republic. Konanki vanished during a spring break trip, and Ribe has given conflicting accounts of the night’s events. The FBI and local authorities are intensifying their search efforts.
title: Indian-origin student disappears: 24-year old named 'person of interest'

description: India was the fifth most polluted country globally in 2024, with Byrnihat in Meghalaya being the most polluted metropolitan area. Despite a 7% decline in PM2.5 concentrations compared to 2023, major urban centers like New Delhi continued to face severe air pollution problems.
title: Meghalaya city tops global air pollution list; India No. 5

description: Deputy CM Ajit Pawar urged political leaders to exercise caution in their statements after Fisheries Minister Nitesh Rane claimed Muslims were not in Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj's army. Pawar emphasized that historical research confirms Muslim participation in Shivaji Maharaj’s forces, noting their patriotic contributions.
title: 'Muslims part of Shivaji's army': Ajit Pawar advises restrain after Rane's comments

description: Sunil Chhetri's return to the national team has sparked a mix of hope and questions among Indian football fans. Despite his age, his leadership is seen as a potential boost for the team. The article examines the challenges faced by Indian football in finding a successor and the broader need for structural development.
title: The good and not so good about Sunil Chhetri's comeback

description: A 19-year-old college student, Amogh Seth, was fatally shot in Lakhimpur Kheri after being chased and attacked by six men, including the main suspect, Anmol Puri. The incident occurred near a police outpost. Amogh had earlier insulted Anmol, leading to the latter seeking revenge. Two suspects have been detained while Anmol remains at large.
title: BBA student made to run 500m, hunted down and shot dead in UP

description: The Indian stock market has seen a dramatic fall, with BSE Sensex and Nifty50 losing over $1 trillion in market value in four months, driven by domestic economic challenges. Despite this downturn, Morgan Stanley predicts the Sensex to reach 105,000 points by December 2025, citing India's stable earnings growth.
title: $1 trillion wiped out! Indian stock market crash shrinks share in global cap
Astronomers discover 128 new moons around Saturn

description: DMK MP Kanimozhi accused Education Minister Dharmendra Pradhan of misrepresenting Tamil Nadu's stance on PM-SHRI schools, clarifying they never agreed to the three-language policy or NEP fully. This follows Pradhan's claim of TN staging the language controversy to gain political points. Union Minister Nirmala Sitharaman also weighed in, criticizing the DMK's perceived hypocrisy.
title: 'Stop twisting facts': DMK counters Centre's 'consent' claim amid three-language showdown

description: Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) has acquired Darshita Southern India Happy Homes in an all-cash deal valued at Rs 2,250 crore. TCS will transform the acquired land and building into a delivery centre in Bengaluru. Darshita Southern India Happy Homes is a commercial real estate firm, currently in development, with no revenue generation reported in the past three years.
title: TCS acquires commercial real estate company
Vice President Jagdeep Dhankhar discharged from AIIMS after three days

description: A case has been filed against three men for assaulting a Dalit groom and threatening to kill him if he did not dismount his horse during his wedding procession in Agra. The accused also hurled casteist slurs, broke portraits of Dr BR Ambedkar and Gautam Buddha, and attacked the groom's grandfather.
title: Dalit groom on horse assaulted, hit with pistol butt in UP, 3 booked

description: Elon Musk is appealing to reinstate his $56 billion compensation package from Tesla after it was voided by a Delaware court, arguing that legal errors were made. The 2018 pay deal, heavily tied to Tesla's stock performance, was ruled unfair to investors despite being approved by shareholders twice.
title: Defies common sense and… : Elon Musk to court on his $56 billion Tesla salary

description: Maharashtra minister Nitesh Rane supports Malhar certification as an alternative to halal mutton for Hindus, claiming it aligns with Hindu practices. His comments received criticism from Congress MLA Nana Patole, who called for the Chief Minister to take action. BJP MLA Sanjay Upadhyay backed Rane, citing health concerns about halal practices. The initiative aims to promote Hindu-owned mutton shops.
title: 'Eating halal not written in Hindu religion': Rane proposes 'Malhar certification'

description: Ranjeet Prasad, an Indian origin former PA youth worker in Singapore, has been convicted of sexually assaulting a 16-year-old boy in 2007, receiving a 10-year and six-month prison sentence. He exploited the teenager's aspirations and abused his authority, with the court noting his lack of remorse.
title: Indian-origin worker gets over 10 year imprisonment for assaulting teen in Singapore

description: The study published in the Obesity Science and Practice journal found that ultra-processed foods (UPFs) significantly contribute to weight gain. By reducing UPFs in their diet, participants consumed 600 fewer daily calories and lost an average of 3.5 kg over eight weeks. Transitioning to healthier options involves gradual swaps like replacing sugary drinks and cooking homemade meals.
title: Removing this food from diet can help reduce almost 4 kilos, say scientists

description: The former Ausralia captain believes Rohit Sharma has decided not to retire from ODIs following India's triumph in the ICC Champions Trophy because he has his sights set on the next ODI World Cup in 2027. Putting all speculation around his retirement to bed, Rohit said he is not going to retire and sent a clear message that he firmly believes he can still deliver at the top level, while continuing to lead the team.
title: 'Rohit wants one more crack at ODI World Cup'

description: Trump's 25% tariff on steel and aluminum imports, effective Wednesday, aims to boost US factory jobs despite market concerns. Exemptions are removed, and aluminum tariffs increased to 10%. These measures may challenge Indian steel manufacturers and prompt international trade disputes, while US domestic steel producers may benefit from higher prices and market access.
title: Trump's 25% tariffs on steel and aluminum imports take effect: Impact on India

description: Jio Platforms has partnered with SpaceX to offer Starlink's high-speed internet services in India, pending regulatory approval. This collaboration aims to enhance Jio's broadband offerings, ensuring affordable, seamless connectivity across the country. The partnership also explores additional cooperation to boost India's digital ecosystem.
title: Jio partners with Elon Musk's Starlink: 'Jio's top priority is...,' says CEO
Second batch of 266 Indians airlifted from Myanmar scam centres, 549 rescued till now

description: US President Trump dismissed recession fears, asserting confidence in economic growth despite recent market turbulence. He emphasized his approach will yield significant results. His comments followed Tesla's share price decline, amidst Wall Street's volatile performance due to uncertainties in tariff policies. Analysts caution that trade uncertainties may continue to impact markets.
title: 'Trump is always right': US President dismisses recession fears

description: Yuzvendra Chahal, known for his humour and wicket-taking skills, joins Punjab Kings for IPL 2025. Despite a strong IPL 2024 season with 18 wickets, he was not retained by Rajasthan Royals. Now with PBKS, Chahal aims for a national team comeback, starting with impressive domestic performances in the Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy.
title: Watch: Chahal trolls Rizwan with iconic one-liner

description: A woman and her friends in Moradabad's Bhojpur area are accused of killing a cat deemed to bring bad fortune. The group recorded and shared the incident on social media. They face charges under the Wildlife Protection Act, facing up to three years in prison and a Rs 1 lakh fine. Authorities are seeking her and accomplices.
title: Cat killed, set on fire for 'bringing misfortune' by crossing UP woman's path

description: Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian refuses to negotiate a nuclear deal with the US amidst threats from President Donald Trump. Trump's maximum pressure campaign and letter to Iran’s Supreme Leader Ayatollah Khamenei expressing his willingness to negotiate a deal have been met with rejection from Iranian leaders.
title: 'Do whatever the hell you want': Iran President rejects Trump's proposal

description: Head coach Gautam Gambhir plans to travel with India 'A' team to England before the senior team's tour to monitor the reserve pool and prepare for major tournaments including WTC, T20, and ODI World Cups. Emphasizing separate focus on T20 and ODI formats, Gambhir aims to revive India 'A' tours and develop a solid player pool for future competitions.
title: Exclusive: Gautam Gambhir to travel with India 'A' to England

description: A Dhaka court has ordered the seizure of former Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina's residence and other properties owned by her family, and frozen 124 bank accounts linked to them. This action follows an application by the Anti-Corruption Commission. Bangladesh's ministry of foreign affairs has protested false statements by Hasina.
title: Former Bangladesh PM Sheikh Hasina's home seized, family assets frozen

description: The Indian embassy in the United States has issued a warning about fraud calls from scammers pretending to be from the embassy. These callers claim there are errors in passports or visa forms, demanding money for corrections and threatening deportation or imprisonment. The embassy advises the public to ignore these calls and not to share personal information or transfer money.
title: Indian embassy in US warns against fraud calls impersonating officials

description: In Pakistan's Balochistan province, armed militants hijacked a passenger train, killing three people and taking over 450 hostages. Security forces responded swiftly, rescuing more than 100 passengers and killing 16 militants. The Baloch Liberation Army claimed responsibility for the attack, which unfolded as militants targeted the train by blowing up the railway track.
title: Train hijack: Over 100 hostages rescued; 20 Pak soldiers, 16 militants killed

description: NHL insider Chris Johnston provided an important update on Florida Panthers forward Brad Marchand's recovery after his trade from the Boston Bruins. Marchand's return is anticipated closely by fans as his presence could be pivotal for the Panthers' playoff hopes. Marchand's transition to the Panthers remains a point of intrigue given his long tenure with the Bruins.
title: Brad Marchand injury update: NHL insider reveals key details

description: Stock market recommendations: Mehul Kothari from Anand Rathi Shares recommends buying Tube Investments, Godrej Agrovet Ltd, and Astrazeneca Pharma. Each stock has shown signs of positive movement.
title: Buy or Sell: Stock recommendations for today

description: The White House criticized tariffs imposed on US products by India and Canada, highlighting significant tariffs on American alcohol and agricultural goods by India. President Trump advocates for fair trade, hinting at potential tariff increases to counteract what he views as unfair international trade practices.
title: 'India imposes 150% tariff on American alcohol': White House

description: US Vice President JD Vance, along with his wife Usha Vance, will visit India later this month. This marks Vance's second international trip after criticizing European leaders at the Munich Security Conference. Usha Vance, of Indian origin with a strong legal background, brings cultural significance to the visit.
title: 'US VP JD Vance and Usha Vance to visit India next month'

description: President Donald Trump has expressed his intent to classify violent protesters at Tesla dealerships as domestic terrorists. Accompanied by Tesla CEO Elon Musk, Trump emphasized his commitment to protecting American companies from such acts, while also purchasing a Tesla Model S to show support for Musk amid massive protests and boycott calls.
title: Violence at Tesla dealerships to be labeled 'domestic terrorism': Trump

description: Former Pakistan cricketer Shahid Afridi criticises PCB for poor decisions, claiming Pakistan cricket is in 'ICU.' He questions Shadab Khan's recall, citing lack of standout performances. Afridi highlights a lack of continuity and accountability within PCB, and the damaging blame culture that affects players and staff. He urges PCB Chairman Mohsin Naqvi to focus on one job.
title: Afridi slams PCB, says 'Pakistan cricket is in ICU because ...'

description: The historical drama ‘Chhaava’ featuring Vicky Kaushal celebrates a 26-day successful box office run, with a total collection of ₹530.95 crore. Despite a slow fourth week, the film aims to reach ₹600 crore, bolstered by its Telugu release. Directed by Laxman Utekar, it surpasses collections of ‘Gadar 2’ and ‘Baahubali 2’, becoming Vicky Kaushal’s highest-grossing film.
title: ‘Chhaava’ collection: Vicky Kaushal starrer aims at Rs 600 crore

description: India's Champions Trophy 2025 victory inspired a hilarious video with Hardik Pandya, Arshdeep Singh, and Harshit Rana recreating the iconic meme, ‘Final match. You perform. What happening?’ in Dubai. With significant contributions from Rohit Sharma, Axar Patel, KL Rahul, and Shreyas Iyer, India secured a win over New Zealand, adding humor to their celebratory mood.
title: 'Final match. You perform. What Happening?': Meme recreated - Watch

description: In recent years, the Jaffar Express has faced multiple attacks by Baloch rebels and TTP, causing numerous casualties. These attacks highlight the ongoing insurgency in Balochistan and the rising use of suicide bombings by BLA, particularly targeting Chinese nationals and Pakistani forces. The increased frequency and intensity of these attacks pose significant challenges for the Pakistani government.
title: Pakistan train hijack: Jaffar Express a hot target for BLA for years now

description: The US Education Department is cutting its workforce by nearly 50%, affecting hundreds of employees and closing several regional offices. This move is part of President Trump's proposal to eliminate the department, aiming to decentralize education and return power to states, students, and families.
title: Trump administration crackdown on Education Department, halves workforce

description: Madras High Court ruled that temple land could be acquired for the Chennai Metro Rail project if it benefits devotees, rejecting a PIL against the acquisition. The court also criticized CMRL’s plan to take over United India Insurance's land, noting it violated natural justice principles since the company was not properly informed.
title: 'God will forgive': Madras HC allows acquisition of two temple lands

description: OpenAI has signed a five-year, $11.9 billion deal with CoreWeave, enhancing their cloud computing capabilities with over 250,000 Nvidia GPUs. The agreement signals a shift from OpenAI's reliance on Microsoft and supports CoreWeave's upcoming IPO. This move underscores the evolving AI landscape as OpenAI seeks more computing power and diverse infrastructure.
title: This may be '$12 bln proof' that all is not well between Microsoft & OpenAI

description: Chandrasekhar Reddy, a former lecturer, and his wife reportedly killed their two children before taking their own lives due to financial struggles. Police recovered a suicide note detailing their hardships. The family, originally from Wanaparthy, had recently moved to Hyderabad. Investigations are ongoing, and a case has been registered.
title: 'Poisoned son, throttled daughter': Ex-lecturer, wife kill kids, before suicide

description: Tourism-related stocks took a significant hit on Tuesday after major US airlines issued warnings about declining travel demand. Expedia Group shares fell by 8%, and Airbnb stock also dropped. Despite the sector's downturn, Southwest Airlines shares climbed due to new revenue-generating initiatives.
title: Why Expedia Group, Airbnb & other travel stocks are seeing biggest-ever fall

description: In Jhunjhunu's Soti village, a young man named Ankit Kumar bravely descended into a 120-foot-deep dry well to rescue a cat trapped for five days. Despite the well's damage and the cat's initial resistance, Ankit's persistent efforts successfully saved the feline. The cat, though shaken, ultimately dashed to safety, thanks to the commendable rescue mission.
title: Watch: Rajasthan man descends into 120-feet well to rescue stranded cat

description: Airtel gains a competitive edge by entering a partnership with Elon Musk’s Starlink to market broadband and internet satellite services in India. This will enhance Airtel’s existing network and expand coverage to remote areas, awaiting regulatory approval. This collaboration signifies Airtel’s commitment to providing reliable internet connectivity across the country.
title: Airtel deal with Musk’s Starlink to bring high-speed net to India

description: The Election Commission has asked for suggestions from political parties on unresolved voter list and photo identity card issues by April 30. Delegations from BJP, TMC, and BJD have raised concerns about duplicate voters and EPIC numbers. The Commission aims to address these issues and strengthen electoral processes through interactions with party leaders.
title: Amid row over EPIC & voter lists, EC invites suggestions from all parties

description: The Gauhati High Court has ruled that fruit pulp and juice-based carbonated drinks fall under the lower 12% GST slab instead of the higher 28%. This ruling benefits manufacturers like X’SS Beverage by classifying these drinks based on their essential fruit juice content rather than their carbonation.
title: Carbonated juices to attract 12% GST, not 28%: High court

description: Congress has stated that states which controlled population will lose seats due to delimitation based on population criteria. States like Tamil Nadu, Kerala, and Andhra Pradesh are expected to lose seats, while Uttar Pradesh, Bihar, and Rajasthan are among the gainers. Tamil Nadu's chief minister has invited various parties to join a joint action committee against this exercise.
title: Delimitation will punish states that controlled population: Congress

description: Finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman accused DMK of hypocrisy regarding the Tamil language controversy while defending her colleague. The Lok Sabha passed supplementary demands for grants, including Rs 51,463 crore additional spending. She assured financial support for Manipur's economic development and criticized TMC’s Kriti Azad for not addressing corruption issues in West Bengal.
title: Finance minister Sitharaman tables Manipur budget, then launches DMK attack

description: An Indian startup's space surveillance satellite, SCOT, was commissioned last Saturday after capturing images over South America. Bengaluru-based Digantara launched SCOT on January 14 aboard SpaceX’s Transporter-12 rocket. The satellite tracks objects as small as 5cm in Earth's orbit and captured a stunning image featuring the city of Buenos Aires.
title: Indian startup’s commercial space surveillance sat begins operations

description: A heated exchange occurred in Rajya Sabha over Congress leader Mallikarjun Kharge's controversial remark, 'aapko theek se thokenge.' BJP demanded an apology and expungement of the remark. Kharge later apologized, clarifying his comments were directed at government policies, not the Chair.
title: Kharge’s ‘thokenge’ barb stirs a different ‘language row’ in Rajya Sabha

description: Lalit Modi challenges Vanuatu government's decision to revoke his passport in court. Modi, currently in Vanuatu, has appealed the cancellation of his citizenship. India's high commission in London had refused his request to surrender his Indian passport. Vanuatu's Citizenship Commission will await the court's outcome before proceeding with citizenship revocation.
title: Lalit Modi moves Vanuatu court against his passport cancellation

description: Home Minister Amit Shah has announced an investment of Rs 2.5 lakh crore in the NorthEast, aiming to prevent youth migration for employment within the next 10 years. The Modi government has significantly increased the region's budget and improved infrastructure, resulting in a 70% reduction in violent incidents and the surrender of 10,500 insurgents.
title: No youth from NE will have to migrate for work in next 10 years: Amit Shah

description: Opposition parties continued their protests in and outside Parliament over issues like duplicate EPIC numbers, the three-language formula, and delimitation. TMC, Congress, and BJD walked out of Rajya Sabha, while TMC and BJD approached the Election Commission. DMK MPs protested the three-language policy, and Congress MPs from Tamil Nadu joined them.
title: Oppn keeps up delimitation, EPIC, NEP offensive in Parl but doesn’t lay siege

description: Tamil Nadu Chief Minister MK Stalin has condemned the National Education Policy (NEP), labeling it a 'destructive plan of Nagpur.' At a welfare meeting in Chengalpattu, Stalin criticized the policy for pushing students out of education, encouraging privatization, and imposing communalism. He reiterated DMK's refusal to accept NEP, despite any financial incentives.
title: Stalin terms NEP ‘destructive plan of Nagpur’, vows DMK will never accept it

description: A viral video shows MS Dhoni, Suresh Raina, and Rishabh Pant dancing to 'Dama Dam Mast Qalandar' during Pant's sister Sakshi's sangeet ceremony in Mussoorie. The cricketers enjoyed the celebrations, with Dhoni making a rare public appearance. Fans are thrilled by this cheerful off-field moment ahead of the upcoming IPL season.
title: Viral video: Dhoni, Raina, and Pant set the dance floor on fire

description: India ranked as the fifth most polluted country worldwide in 2024, with Byrnihat in Meghalaya being the most polluted metropolitan area globally. High pollution levels are linked to rapid industrialisation and unregulated emissions. Despite some improvement, Delhi remains the most polluted capital, and India's cities continue to exceed WHO PM2.5 guidelines.
title: With 13 of 20 most polluted cities, India ranks 5th globally

description: Mumbai recorded its first near 40-degree temperature as the IMD Santacruz observatory noted a maximum of 39.2 degrees, surpassing last March's highest temperature. A heatwave warning for Mumbai, Thane, and Raigad was issued, predicting hot and humid conditions. Temperatures might dip soon due to the late arrival of the sea breeze, bringing some relief.
title: First time this year, Mumbai nears 40°C; IMD issues heatwave warning
